<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="326" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1150,1463]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1186,1211]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Exognath of third maxilliped between 
<number box="[755,859,1186,1211]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" value="0.6499999999999999" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.6">0.6 to 0.7</number>
times the length of endognath ischium. G 
<number box="[1329,1339,1187,1211]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" value="1.0">1</number>
straight, spermatic channel emerging on cephalic side; subdistal portion of mesio-cephalic, lateral sides with field of minute spines; marginal suture on mesial side, straight along most of stem; marginal process simple, short; distal part with large mesial lobe, narrow lateral lobe; field of apical spines weakly developed on internal surface of lateral lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="326" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1150,1463]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1330,1355]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Distribution</emphasis>
. The species of this genus are distributed in southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[987,1109,1330,1355]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and western 
<collectingCountry box="[1256,1348,1331,1354]" name="Panama" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Panama</collectingCountry>
, Pacific drainage.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
